http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/16-held-for-damaging-railway-property/article13979340.ece

The Government Railway Police on Sunday arrested 16 youth on charges of damaging railway property at the Pazhavanthangal railway station .A police official said the 16 youngsters went on a rampage of breaking 22 tube lights and a fan on the night of January 1. Based on a complaint filed by the staff at the railway station, a case was filed.Except a 20-year-old, the rest of the youth are aged between 12 and 16. They are residents of Kannan Colony in Pazhavanthangal.A case under Section 151 of the Indian Railway Act (damaging railway property) has been registered.